{
  "texts": [
    "Eerola et al. (2020) evaluated various ways to implement the padding and padding with the mode of the image (the most common color in the image typically corresponding to the background color) produced the best results on IFCB data.",
    "Both approaches (forgoing and maintaining aspect ratio) have been utilized in plankton recognition.",
    "However, there exists little comparison between them.",
    "Dai et al. (2016a) tested various resizing methods were tested on zooplankton images and the best accuracy was obtained by maintaining the aspect ratio while scaling.",
    "On the other hand, Jindal and Mundra (2015) found little to no difference on performance between the approaches despite images appearing distorted when forgoing aspect ratio."
  ]
}